{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, the performance for CBT_Stage3, Nie et al.",
    "As mentioned before, CBT Guide needs to be aware of cognitive distortions and point them out to guide effectively.According to psychotherapists' experiences, identifying unhelpful thoughts is the most challenging stage within the three stages of the CBT process, with the highest probability of containing cognitive distortions and less information obtained from the user in this stage.",
    "Table 4 shows the performance of different LLMs in providing appropriate CBT Guide when responses are invalid in the three CBT stages.",
    "In general, using the same prompt, GPT-3.5 Turbo performs the best, even outperforming GPT-4.",
    "Therapists comment that \"GPT-4 sometimes sounds like it is reading into the user's feelings\" instead of guiding the user objectively."
  ]
}